Statistical Spell Checker

Gabriel Dulac-Arnold <gabe@squirrelsoup.net> [CS09F004]
Johannes H. Jensen <johannj@stud.ntnu.no> [CS09F005]


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------


For information on the theory behind the spellchecker, please see the report.

All the code can be found in the src/ directory. The programs depend on Python
and the Natural Language Toolkit (http://www.nltk.org).

The following programs are provided:

main.py	--	Main program for running spellchecker against test cases.
			Usage: ./main.py <input.xml> <output.csv>

spel.py	--	Program for simple testing of the spellchecker.
			spel.py reads sentences from standard input and prints a list
			of misspelled words and provides weighted candidate suggestions.


count_words.py			--	Count words in corpus and output to stdout
count_word_bigrams.py	--	Count word bigrams in corpus and output to stdout


For generating the word and bigram counts the brown and reuters corpora need
to be installed to NLTK. This can be done with the command

	python -c 'import nltk; nltk.download()'

Happy testing!
